href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-bluehost-alternatives/\">7 Best Bluehost Alternatives for 2019 (Compared &#038; Reviewed)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17645:\"<p>Looking for a Bluehost alternative to host your site? Bluehost is one of the most popular website hosting services on the market. It’s officially recommended by WordPress.org as well, adding to its well-earned reputation as a trusted web hosting provider.</p>\n<p>But, just because Bluehost is popular, doesn’t mean that it&#8217;s the right choice for your individual needs. In this article, we’ll show you the top 7 Bluehost alternatives so you can make an informed decision on the best hosting for your site.</p>\n<h3>Why Bluehost Alternatives?</h3>\n<p>While Bluehost is one of the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/\">leading web hosting providers</a> that we often recommend, here&#8217;re a few reasons why some of our users want to try out a Bluehost alternative.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>No email-based support</strong>: In an effort to focus on providing instant support, Bluehost has discontinued email-based support. This can be frustrating when you want to fix advanced issues that may take a bit longer to resolve.</li>\n<li><strong>A monthly billing option isn’t available</strong>: When you subscribe to a Bluehost plan, you must choose at least a 12-month plan.</li>\n<li><strong>No website builder</strong>: Unlike most companies on the cheap hosting vertical, Bluehost doesn’t offer a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-website-builders-for-beginners-compared/\">website builder</a> with any of their plans.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Not interested in signing up for a Bluehost hosting plan? No worries!</p>\n<p>Below are a few different Bluehost alternatives that you might find more appealing. Before dive in, let’s take a look at our hosting review process.</p>\n<h3>About Our Top Bluehost Alternatives Review Process</h3>\n<p>We wrote this Bluehost alternatives review with a single goal in mind: help you easily choose the best Bluehost alternative for your website.</p>\n<p>Unlike other sites, we’ve actually signed up for some of the most popular hosting services on the market to evaluate their performance.</p>\n<p>Here’s exactly what we did:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Signed up with the top Bluehost alternative companies on the market</li>\n<li>Created a test WordPress site</li>\n<li>Installed a WordPress theme and added dummy content, including images, to mirror the actual live site environment on those test accounts</li>\n<li>Conducted a few different speed tests to see how the site would perform and recorded the test data</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Top 7 Best Bluehost Alternatives (2019)</h3>\n<p>Let’s get straight to the top Bluehost alternatives starting with #1 on our list.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/siteground-review.png\" alt=\"siteground review\" width=\"370\" height=\"227\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221580\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/siteground-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/siteground-review-300x184.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. SiteGround</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 649 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.98%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 10/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SiteGround.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with SiteGround &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>Looking for a FAST Bluehost alternative? If speed is your top priority, then look no further than SiteGround. SiteGround is trusted by the owners of over 1 million domains.</p>\n<p>Unlike Bluehost, they offer 24/7 support via phone, live chat, and email-based tickets. You’ll also get free Cloudflare CDN, a website builder, and cPanel + SSH access with any of their plans.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Our users pay <del>$11.95</del> $3.95 per month (67% off)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/siteground-review/\">Read our SiteGround review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/hostgator-review.png\" alt=\"hostgator review\" width=\"370\" height=\"220\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221576\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/hostgator-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/hostgator-review-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. HostGator</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 691 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.96%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 10/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">HostGator.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with HostGator &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>HostGator provides you with more hosting options than Bluehost, such as shared hosting, cloud hosting, WordPress hosting, reseller hosting, etc. Their website builder lets you choose from over 100+ mobile-friendly templates.</p>\n<p>HostGator offers free transfers with all of their hosting plans within 30 days of signing up. They also offer AdWords and Bing credits to help grow your website along with 24/7 support via phone, chat, and tickets.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Our users pay <del>$6.95</del> $2.78 per month (60% off + free SSL)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/hostgator-review/\">Read our HostGator review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/dreamhost-review.png\" alt=\"dreamhost review\" width=\"370\" height=\"222\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221574\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/dreamhost-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/dreamhost-review-300x180.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Dreamhost</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 445 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.90%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 7/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dreamhost.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with DreamHost &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>Just like Bluehost, DreamHost is also an officially recommended WordPress hosting service. They’re independently operated, unlike Bluehost, and have nearly 20 years of experience in web hosting.</p>\n<p>They provide you with a whopping 97-day money back guarantee, allowing you to try their hosting services risk-free. Best of all, with DreamHost, you can opt for a monthly plan if you’d like.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Our users pay only <del>$10.95</del> $2.59 per month (Free SSL + 76% off)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/dreamhost-review/\">Read our Dreamhost review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/ipage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ipage-review.png\" alt=\"ipage review\" width=\"370\" height=\"217\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221578\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ipage-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ipage-review-300x176.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/ipage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. iPage</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 2.60 s</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.98%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 8/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/ipage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">iPage.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/ipage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with iPage &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>Do you think Bluehost is an overpriced hosting service? Then you might want to consider iPage.</p>\n<p>iPage is one of the cheapest (yet reliable) web hosting services on the market. With iPage, you can start a website for as low as $1.99 per month. They provide you with a basic drag and drop builder with limited features. They also offer $200 worth of free ad credits which Bluehost doesn’t.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Our users pay <del>$7.99</del> $1.99 per month (75% off + free domain name and SSL)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/ipage-review/\">Read our iPage review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/greengeeks-review.png\" alt=\"greengeeks review\" width=\"370\" height=\"245\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221575\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/greengeeks-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/greengeeks-review-300x199.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. GreenGeeks</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 697 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.92%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 9/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">GreenGeeks.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with GreenGeeks &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>GreenGeeks is the world’s #1 eco-friendly web hosting provider. Unlike Bluehost and most other web hosting providers, GreenGeeks doesn’t upsell addon services with their hosting plans.</p>\n<p>GreenGeeks automatically updates your WordPress installs so you can have peace of mind knowing your website is secure. GreenGeeks offers US-based technical support via phone, live chat, and email/tickets.</p>\n<p><strong>Price</strong>: Our users pay <del>$9.95</del> $2.95 per month (Free domain name + 70% off)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/greengeeks-review/\">Read our GreenGeeks review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/inmotion-hosting-review.png\" alt=\"inmotion hosting review\" width=\"370\" height=\"202\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221577\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/inmotion-hosting-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/inmotion-hosting-review-300x164.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. InMotion Hosting</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 982 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.91%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 9/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">InMotionHosting.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with InMotion Hosting &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>InMotion Hosting comes with a lot of desirable hosting features such as a WordPress-optimized platform with server caching and SSD storage. They offer an unmatched 90-day money back guarantee to try out their service risk-free.</p>\n<p>Unlike other hosting providers, InMotion Hosting offers a WordPress-based page builder known as BoldGrid so you can quickly <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\">build a flexible website</a> with WordPress via the drag and drop editor.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Our users pay only <del>$7.99</del> $4.99 per month (37% off + free domain name)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/inmotion-hosting-review/\">Read our InMotion Hosting review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/a2hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/a2-hosting-review.png\" alt=\"a2 hosting review\" width=\"370\" height=\"206\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-221573\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/a2-hosting-review.png 370w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/a2-hosting-review-300x167.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 370px) 100vw, 370px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/a2hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. A2 Hosting</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Load time</strong>: 1.28 s</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.90%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 9/10</li>\n<li><strong>Website</strong>: A2hosting.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/a2hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Get started with A2 Hosting &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>A2 Hosting is one of the best developer-friendly hosting services on the market. A2 Hosting lets you choose from 2 great operating system options: Linux and Windows. Their data centers are located around the globe in 3 different continents, so you can rest assured that your web pages are served quickly.</p>\n<p>Best of all, they provide you with an industry-leading anytime money back guarantee by which you can get a full refund for unused services at any time.</p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Our users pay only <del>$7.99</del> $3.92 per month (50% off)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/a2-hosting-review/\">Read our A2 Hosting review &raquo;</a></p>\n<h3>Recap: Top 7 Bluehost Alternatives</h3>\n\n<table id=\"tablepress-19\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-19\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"row-1 odd\">\n	<th class=\"column-1\">WordPress Hosting</th><th class=\"column-2\">Cost</th><th class=\"column-3\">Money Back</th><th class=\"column-4\">Load Time</th><th class=\"column-5\">Uptime</th><th class=\"column-6\">Support</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\n<tr class=\"row-2 even\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>1. SiteGround</strong></a></td><td class=\"column-2\"><strong>$3.95/mo.</strong></td><td class=\"column-3\"><strong>30 days</strong></td><td class=\"column-4\"><strong>649 ms</strong></td><td class=\"column-5\"><strong>99.98%</strong></td><td class=\"column-6\"><strong>10/10</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row-3 odd\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>2. HostGator</strong></a></td><td class=\"column-2\"><strong>$2.78/mo.</strong></td><td class=\"column-3\"><strong>45 days</strong></td><td class=\"column-4\"><strong>691 ms</strong></td><td class=\"column-5\"><strong>99.96%</strong></td><td class=\"column-6\"><strong>10/10</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row-4 even\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Dreamhost</a></td><td class=\"column-2\">$2.59/mo.</td><td class=\"column-3\">97 days</td><td class=\"column-4\">445 ms</td><td class=\"column-5\">99.90%</td><td class=\"column-6\">7/10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row-5 odd\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/ipage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. iPage</a></td><td class=\"column-2\">$1.99/mo.</td><td class=\"column-3\">30 days</td><td class=\"column-4\">2600 ms</td><td class=\"column-5\">99.98%</td><td class=\"column-6\">8/10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row-6 even\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. GreenGeeks</a></td><td class=\"column-2\">$3.49/mo.</td><td class=\"column-3\">30 days</td><td class=\"column-4\">697 ms</td><td class=\"column-5\">99.92%</td><td class=\"column-6\">9/10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row-7 odd\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. InMotion Hosting</a></td><td class=\"column-2\">$3.49/mo.</td><td class=\"column-3\">90 days</td><td class=\"column-4\">982 ms</td><td class=\"column-5\">99.91%</td><td class=\"column-6\">9/10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row-8 even\">\n	<td class=\"column-1\"><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/a2hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. A2 Hosting</a></td><td class=\"column-2\">$3.92/mo.</td><td class=\"column-3\">30 days</td><td class=\"column-4\">1280 ms</td><td class=\"column-5\">99.90%</td><td class=\"column-6\">9/10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<!-- #tablepress-19 from cache -->\n<p>We hope this article helped you find the best Bluehost alternative for your site.</p>\n<p>You might also want to check out our <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-start-a-blog-step-by-step/\">ultimate guide to starting a blog</a>.</p>\n<p>So which web host do you like the most? Share your thoughts with us in the comments section.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-bluehost-alternatives/\">7 Best Bluehost Alternatives for 2019 (Compared &#038; Reviewed)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-bluehost-alternatives/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"Wix Review 2019 – Is It Better than WordPress? [TESTED]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wix-review/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wix-review/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 15 Jan 2019 10:58:20 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Resources\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"blogging platform\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"free website builder\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"website builder\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=228243\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:596:\"<p>Are you planning to create your first website? Do you want to start it for free? Then, Wix is a great platform to consider. Wix is a simple, beginner-friendly website builder that allows you to build a website easily without worrying about code. In this Wix review, we’ll examine various aspects of the platform including [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wix-review/\">Wix Review 2019 &#8211; Is It Better than WordPress? [TESTED]</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28854:\"<p>Are you planning to create your first website? Do you want to start it for free? Then, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> is a great platform to consider. Wix is a simple, beginner-friendly website builder that allows you to build a website easily without worrying about code. </p>\n<p>In this Wix review, we’ll examine various aspects of the platform including its features, functionalities, pricing, and more, to help you decide if it&#8217;s right for your website needs. </p>\n<h3>About Wix</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> is a simple website builder that allows you to create any type of website with ease. You can quickly <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-start-a-blog-step-by-step/\">create a beautiful blog</a>, online store, business website, portfolio, photography site, or any other type of website using Wix. </p>\n<p>It comes with an easy-to-use <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-page-builders-compared/\">drag and drop builder</a> with which you can customize anything and everything on your site and build the design you want. If you want an even easier option, you can use Wix Artificial Design Intelligence (ADI) which builds a personalized website for you based on your answers to a few simple questions. For advanced users, there’s also the Wix Code option. </p>\n<p>Wix is a fully-hosted platform which includes <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/difference-between-domain-name-and-web-hosting-revealed/\">hosting and domain services</a> for you. In addition, it’ll handle your website security, and provides you with easy <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-seo-tools-to-grow-your-site-traffic/\">tools for search engine optimization (SEO)</a>. In other words, it’s a full package website building service, which is great for beginners. </p>\n<p>Wix.com was founded in 2006 with the goal to empower anyone to create their own website. It now has over 110 million users across 190 countries. It’s currently one the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-website-builders-for-beginners-compared-2018/\">most widely-used website builders</a> and utilizes the second most-used cloud-based website builder technology. </p>\n<h3>Getting Started with Wix</h3>\n<p>To start making your new website on Wix, you’ll need to visit the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">official Wix website</a> and click the <strong>Get Started</strong> button. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/get-started-with-wix.jpg\" alt=\"get-started-with-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"489\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227599\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/get-started-with-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/get-started-with-wix-300x189.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/get-started-with-wix-768x485.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In the next screen, you’ll see the <strong>Log In</strong> or <strong>Sign Up</strong> options. Since you’re just starting out, you’ll need to choose <strong>Sign Up</strong>. </p>\n<p>Then, you’ll need to insert your email address and a new password for your Wix account. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/sign-up-wix.jpg\" alt=\"sign-up-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"423\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227630\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/sign-up-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/sign-up-wix-300x164.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/sign-up-wix-768x419.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After you enter the required email and password, click the <strong>Sign Up</strong> button. </p>\n<p>On the next screen, you’ll see be asked to answer a few questions; however, you can skip this. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/skip-questions-wix.jpg\" alt=\"skip-questions-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227600\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/skip-questions-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/skip-questions-wix-300x159.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/skip-questions-wix-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you’ll see 2 easy Wix options for building your site: <strong>Wix Artificial Design Intelligence (ADI)</strong> and <strong>Wix Drag and Drop Editor</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor-or-adi.jpg\" alt=\"wix-editor-or-adi\" width=\"775\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227632\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor-or-adi.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor-or-adi-300x159.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor-or-adi-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>If you choose Wix ADI, you’ll be asked a few simple questions, and on the basis of your answers, Wix’ll automatically build a personalized site for you. Whereas, Wix Editor allows you to choose a template, and customize it with their drag and drop builder. When we compared these 2 options, we found Wix ADI easier; so let’s see how that works first. </p>\n<p>Click <strong>Start Now</strong> below the Wix ADI option to proceed. Now, you’ll see the first question: <strong>What type of site do you want to create?</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-type-wix.jpg\" alt=\"choose-site-type-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227601\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-type-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-type-wix-300x159.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-type-wix-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can enter your business name or website type, then choose a suitable option. After that, click <strong>Next</strong>.</p>\n<p>Now, you’ll be shown the features you’re most likely to use on your site. You can check all, some, or none as per your desire. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-features-wix.jpg\" alt=\"choose-site-features-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227602\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-features-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-features-wix-300x159.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-site-features-wix-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve made your choices, click <strong>Next</strong>. </p>\n<p>Then, on the next screen, you’ll be asked to insert the name of your website. Choose the name you’d like to have and enter it there. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/website-name-wix.jpg\" alt=\"website-name-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227603\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/website-name-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/website-name-wix-300x159.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/website-name-wix-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After you fill in your website name, click <strong>Next</strong>. Then, you’ll be asked to enter your physical location. If you think it’s not necessary, you can skip this step. </p>\n<p>Next, you’ll see the <strong>Review and edit your info</strong> page. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/review-edit-info-wix.jpg\" alt=\"review-edit-info-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"492\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227604\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/review-edit-info-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/review-edit-info-wix-300x190.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/review-edit-info-wix-768x488.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can add a new logo for your site, change your website name, email address, add contact details, and social media. Then, click <strong>Next</strong>. </p>\n<p>On the next screen, you’ll be asked to choose a style. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pick-style-wix.jpg\" alt=\"pick-style-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"492\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227605\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pick-style-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pick-style-wix-300x190.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pick-style-wix-768x488.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You’ll need to choose the colors and fonts you want to use via a Style. For this example, we’ll pick <strong>Elegant</strong>. After you make your selection, click <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>\n<p>Then, you’ll be asked if you want to create a color palette from your logo in the next step. You can click <strong>Create Palette</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/create-color-palette-wix.jpg\" alt=\"create-color-palette-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"405\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227606\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/create-color-palette-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/create-color-palette-wix-300x157.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/create-color-palette-wix-768x401.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now it’ll create a unique color palette for your website. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/use-color-palette.jpg\" alt=\"use-color-palette\" width=\"775\" height=\"405\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227607\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/use-color-palette.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/use-color-palette-300x157.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/use-color-palette-768x401.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can click <strong>Use These Colors</strong> to proceed. Then, Wix ADI starts creating your website. It automatically adds the features you’ll need. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-website-making.jpg\" alt=\"wix-website-making\" width=\"775\" height=\"180\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227608\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-website-making.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-website-making-300x70.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-website-making-768x178.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>It adds a blog section, contact section, chat features, and other useful elements. It also makes your site mobile-responsive. </p>\n<p>After the automatic site-making process is completed, you’ll be asked to choose a homepage design. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-homepage-theme-wix.jpg\" alt=\"choose-homepage-theme-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"405\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227609\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-homepage-theme-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-homepage-theme-wix-300x157.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-homepage-theme-wix-768x401.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can choose the design you like the most by clicking it. Next, you’ll a preview of what your finished website could look like. However, you’ll be given edit options for each section or each element if you mouse hover on them. So if the preview isn&#8217;t perfection, feel free to make changes before publishing.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-adi-interface.jpg\" alt=\"wix-site-adi-interface\" width=\"775\" height=\"405\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227610\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-adi-interface.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-adi-interface-300x157.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-adi-interface-768x401.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>If you want to edit anything, like changing the title, adding a description, or changing the header image, you can simply click on the item you want to change. Then, it’ll show an editing panel on the left side and live preview to the right. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-wix-site-adi.jpg\" alt=\"edit-wix-site-adi\" width=\"775\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227611\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-wix-site-adi.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-wix-site-adi-300x194.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-wix-site-adi-768x495.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you can live preview every change you make on the editor. You can edit anything you want. When you’re happy with the design, you can click the <strong>Publish</strong> button at the top. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/publish-wix-site.jpg\" alt=\"publish-wix-site\" width=\"775\" height=\"174\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227612\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/publish-wix-site.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/publish-wix-site-300x67.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/publish-wix-site-768x172.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>In the next screen, you’ll be able to choose a domain name. It has 2 options: use a free Wix subdomain or connect your custom domain. </p>\n<p>For beginners, Wix provides a free Wix subdomain option with which allows you to have a Wix website completely free. Your Wix subdomain will have a format like this: https://username.wixsite.com/sitename. </p>\n<p>For example, you can see in the screenshot below.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-domain-wix.jpg\" alt=\"choose-domain-wix\" width=\"775\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227613\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-domain-wix.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-domain-wix-300x194.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-domain-wix-768x495.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>If you want to use a custom domain name like mystunningwebsite.com, or isitwp.com, you’ll need to subscribe to a Wix premium plan. </p>\n<p>After you add your website name, click <strong>Publish and Continue</strong>. </p>\n<p>Now your free Wix website will be online. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-published.jpg\" alt=\"wix-site-published\" width=\"775\" height=\"466\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227614\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-published.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-published-300x180.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-site-published-768x462.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can now view your site. That’s it! It’ll take you just a few minutes to answer Wix&#8217;s questions, and Wix ADI will do the rest!</p>\n<h3>Wix Editor – Easy to Use Drag and Drop Tool</h3>\n<p>Another easy option for creating a free website in <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> is using the Wix editor, their user-friendly drag and drop builder. </p>\n<p>If you choose Wix Editor, you’ll first need to choose a template to start your site. You can preview the available templates, and choose the one you like most by clicking <strong>Edit</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-edit-wix-template.jpg\" alt=\"choose-edit-wix-template\" width=\"770\" height=\"550\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227615\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-edit-wix-template.jpg 770w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-edit-wix-template-300x214.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/choose-edit-wix-template-768x549.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you’ll see the drag and drop Wix Editor interface open. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor.jpg\" alt=\"wix-editor\" width=\"770\" height=\"536\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227616\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor.jpg 770w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor-300x209.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-editor-768x535.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you can easily change anything simply by clicking directly on any element you want to edit. Then, it’ll open the editing options right there. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-text-wix-editor.jpg\" alt=\"edit-text-wix-editor\" width=\"770\" height=\"528\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227618\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-text-wix-editor.jpg 770w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-text-wix-editor-300x206.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/edit-text-wix-editor-768x527.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also drag and drop any element/ block anywhere within your template. It’s very easy to customize the entire site design with the Wix Editor. </p>\n<p>Once you customize everything you want, click the <strong>Publish</strong> button to make your Wix website live. </p>\n<h3>Wix Code for Advanced Code Capabilities</h3>\n<p>In addition to Wix ADI and Wix Editor, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> has yet another option for creating a free website: Wix Code. This option was specifically designed for professional web developers who have good coding skills. </p>\n<p>Using Wix code, you can customize your entire Wix website design and add more powerful functionalities to it. To get started, you’ll need to turn on <strong>Developer Tools</strong> first. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-code.jpg\" alt=\"wix-code\" width=\"775\" height=\"318\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227619\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-code.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-code-300x123.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-code-768x315.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<h3>Wix Templates</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> features 500+ designer-made professional website templates ready for use. You can find a wide selection of templates for different categories. Some of the categories are: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Business</li>\n<li>Online store</li>\n<li>Travel and tourism</li>\n<li>Blogs and forums</li>\n<li>Landing pages</li>\n<li>Fashion and beauty</li>\n<li>Events</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With the professional-looking themes at Wix, it’s easy and quick to make a stunning website. </p>\n<h3>Wix Marketing Tools</h3>\n<p>After you’ve created a website in <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a>, you’ll need to promote to drive more traffic to it. Fortunately, Wix has powerful marketing tools built in just for you. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-marketing-tools.jpg\" alt=\"wix-marketing-tools\" width=\"775\" height=\"543\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227620\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-marketing-tools.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-marketing-tools-300x210.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-marketing-tools-768x538.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>There’s a user-friendly Wix SEO Wiz to help you boost your website’s rank on Google search results. It’s a step-by-step plan which guides you to improve your site’s visibility online. </p>\n<p>In addition, you’ll find powerful tools for email marketing, social posts, marketing integrations, and logo maker for branding your business. </p>\n<h3>Wix Apps to Grow Your Website</h3>\n<p>To help you add more functionality to your Wix site, you can use Wix apps. There’re over 200 powerful free and premium Wix apps for you to utilize. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-apps.jpg\" alt=\"wix-apps\" width=\"775\" height=\"484\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227621\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-apps.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-apps-300x187.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-apps-768x480.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>These apps are useful for a variety of purposes including analytics, chat, forms, events, bookings, photography, video, music, etc. </p>\n<h3>Wix Pricing and Support</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> has both free and premium plans for making your website. It allows you to build a complete website for free if you’re okay with a Wix subdomain like this: https://username.wixsite.com/sitename. But, if you want to use a professional custom domain name, you’ll need to subscribe to one of their premium plans.</p>\n<p>There’re 5 pricing plans for premium users: </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-pricing.jpg\" alt=\"wix-pricing\" width=\"775\" height=\"464\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227622\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-pricing.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-pricing-300x180.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/wix-pricing-768x460.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>1. Connect Domain</strong>: The most basic plan is called <strong>Connect Domain</strong> which costs $4.50 per month. With this plan, you can connect a custom domain; however, you’ll need to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-register-a-domain-name/\">register a domain</a> on your own first and later connect it with your Wix site. You should also take a look at our article on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/choose-best-domain-name-registrar/\" title=\"How to Choose the Best Domain Name Registrar in 2019\">best domain name registrars</a> to buy a domain.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Combo</strong>: It costs $8.50 per month. With this plan, and all the plans above it, you’ll get a free domain from Wix. However, if you&#8217;ve got a domain already registered, you’ll have the option to connect to it. </p>\n<p><strong>3. Unlimited</strong>: This plan offers unlimited bandwidth, free domain or connect domain, remove Wix ads, customized favicon, etc. It costs $12.50 per month. </p>\n<p><strong>4. eCommerce</strong>: This plan was especially designed for eCommerce sites. It has all the features in the <strong>Unlimited Plan</strong> plus additional online store features. It costs $16.50 per month. </p>\n<p><strong>5. VIP</strong>: It’s the most advanced Wix premium plan. It costs $24 per month. It has all the features in the <strong>eCommerce</strong> plan plus an additional email campaigns option and priority support. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> has a massive collection of articles in the help center for almost any query you might have. You can browse through the articles and get your issues solved in no time. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/wix-help-center.jpg\" alt=\"wix=-help-center\" width=\"745\" height=\"327\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220463\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/wix-help-center.jpg 745w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/wix-help-center-300x132.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px\" /></p>\n<p>However, Wix doesn’t have any instant support options for its basic users. They offer priority support to only the VIP plan users. </p>\n<h3>Wix vs. WordPress – Which Website Platform You Should Use</h3>\n<p>Although <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> gives you an easy way to start a website, you&#8217;ll need to compromise on a number of possibilities that a content management system like WordPress can offer. Here&#8217;re just a few advantages of using WordPress: </p>\n<p><strong>1. Full Control of Your Website and Data</strong></p>\n<p>WordPress allows you to host your website on your own servers; hence, you&#8217;ve full control over your site. Whereas, with Wix, you&#8217;ll have limited control over your site as Wix itself hosts your site. Worst of all, Wix can discontinue their service or suspend your site for any reason at any time.</li>\n<p><strong>2. Boundless Design Possibilities</strong></p>\n<p>WordPress offers you limitless design possibilities with thousands of <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-themes/\">free and premium WordPress themes</a>. There&#8217;re thousands of free themes at the official WordPress.org theme repository, and several more thousands of premium themes at theme marketplaces and third-party theme company websites. On the other hand, Wix has just around 500 templates.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Good Pricing Options</strong></p>\n<p>To start a Wix site with a custom domain name, you&#8217;ll need to buy their <strong>Combo</strong> plan (at least) or get a new domain and connect with their <strong>Connect Domain</strong> plan that costs $8.50 and $4.50 per month respectively. Whereas you can <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\">start a WordPress website</a> for just $2.75 per month with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluehost</a>. </p>\n<p>To learn more, read our <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wix-vs-wordpress/\">full Wix vs. WordPress comparison</a>. </p>\n<h3>Our Verdict on Using Wix for Creating a Free Website</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wix/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wix</a> is one of the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-website-builders-for-beginners-compared/\" title=\"10 Best Website Builders for Beginners Compared\">most popular website builders on the market</a> with easy-to-use features that allow you to build a simple website. It enables anyone to build a simple website or blog to showcase content; however, due to a limited number of templates and tools, you may not find exactly what you need to succeed long term. </p>\n<p>It offers a free website plan for beginners which is good for students to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-start-a-blog-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Start a Blog (and Make Extra Income on the Side)\">start their own blog</a> for free. You can always use the free plan if you&#8217;re okay with an ugly domain with your username appended with wixsite.com/yoursitename. But, if you have to upgrade your site or need a custom domain, the pricing options aren&#8217;t cheap for low-budget users.</p>\n<p>In conclusion, we believe that Wix is a decent website builder platform for creating your first website. But if you wish to establish your own brand or grow your business, a more powerful and more flexible platform like WordPress is the better option. We give Wix 4.5 out of 5 stars. Here&#8217;s the breakdown of our review scores:  </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wix-review/\">Wix Review 2019 &#8211; Is It Better than WordPress? [TESTED]</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wix-review/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"100+ Interesting WordPress Stats &amp; Facts (2019)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://www.isitwp.com/interesting-wordpress-stats-facts/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://www.isitwp.com/interesting-wordpress-stats-facts/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 14 Jan 2019 10:05:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Resources\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"wordpress facts\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"wordpress statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"wordpress stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=228155\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:616:\"<p>Have you been searching for interesting WordPress stats and facts? If you&#8217;re looking into starting a blog or website on WordPress, you might be searching for information about the power of WordPress and some hard evidence of what it can do. Or maybe you&#8217;re a WordPress fan and want to convince others that they should [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/interesting-wordpress-stats-facts/\">100+ Interesting WordPress Stats &#038; Facts (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31653:\"<p>Have you been searching for interesting WordPress stats and facts? If you&#8217;re looking into starting a blog or website on WordPress, you might be searching for information about the power of WordPress and some hard evidence of what it can do. Or maybe you&#8217;re a WordPress fan and want to convince others that they should join the amazing WordPress community and you need stats to back up your claims. Whatever the reason, if you&#8217;re looking for WordPress statistics, you&#8217;re in the right place! </p>\n<p>Get ready to take a deep dive into 100+ interesting WordPress stats and facts. Since this is a master list of WordPress statistics, here&#8217;s a table of contents to help guide you through the article and find the exact statistic or fact you&#8217;re looking for. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-popularity\">The Popularity of WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-development\">WordPress Development</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-community\">The WordPress Community</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-events\">WordPress Events</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-plugins\">WordPress Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-themes\">Themes for WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-security\">WordPress Security</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-economy\">The WordPress Economy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#miscellaneous-wordpress\">Miscellaneous WordPress Stats</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#wordpress-fun\">WordPress Fun Facts</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>First of all, before we jump into these awesome WordPress stats, let&#8217;s talk about the basics of what WordPress is.</p>\n<h3>What is WordPress?</h3>\n<p>WordPress is an online, open source software that you can use to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Make a Website in 2019- Step by Step (with Pictures)\">create a website</a>. It&#8217;s one of the easiest and most powerful content management systems for websites and blogs available today, and it&#8217;s <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-wordpress-complete-wordpress-installation-tutorial/\" target=\"_blank\">free to download and install</a> as well. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WordPress-logotype-alternative.png\" alt=\"what-is-wordpress\" width=\"740\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228188\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WordPress-logotype-alternative.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/WordPress-logotype-alternative-300x162.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s important to note that there are 2 &#8220;types&#8221; of WordPress, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-com-vs-wordpress-org-one-really-better/\">WordPress.org and WordPress.com</a>. Here are the differences between the 2:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>WordPress.org &#8211; WordPress.org is a free software available for download and it can be installed on any <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/wordpress/\" title=\"The Best WordPress Hosting Companies of 2019 (Real Reviews, No B.S)\">WordPress hosting</a> company. </li>\n<li>WordPress.com &#8211; WordPress.com is a hosted solution. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll mostly be focusing on WordPress.org statistics but there are some WordPress.com stats included as well. If you want a more detailed breakdown on the differences between WordPress.org and WordPress.com, check out our article, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-com-vs-wordpress-org-one-really-better/\">WordPress.com vs WordPress.org &#8211; Is One Really Better Than the Other?</a></p>\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s get into these awesome WordPress stats!</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-popularity\">WordPress Popularity &#8211; Statistics, Facts, and Figures</h3>\n<p>WordPress has become the most popular content management system (CMS) in the world. Millions of bloggers and businesses, large and small, have chosen WordPress to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\">start their websites</a>. Here are some statistics and facts that demonstrate the popularity of WordPress.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-popularity.png\" alt=\"wordpress-popularity-stats\" width=\"740\" height=\"372\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228192\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-popularity.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-popularity-300x151.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /> </p>\n<p>1. WordPress powers 32% of the internet. (<a href=\"https://w3techs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">W3Techs</a>)  </p>\n<p>2. Similarly, WordPress powers over 75 million sites on the web. (<a href=\"https://central.wordcamp.org/about/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordCamp</a>)</p>\n<p>3. A Google search of &#8216;WordPress&#8217; gets you about 2,060,000,000 results. (Google)</p>\n<p>4. WordPress&#8217; share of the global content management market is 60.2%. (<a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/wordpress-powers-30-top-10-million-sites-web/242613/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Search Engine Journal</a>)</p>\n<p>5. WordPress gets more monthly unique visitors than Amazon, and the same as Facebook (but with 25x fewer people on staff). (<a href=\"https://www.codeinwp.com/blog/mesmerizing-wordpress-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Codeinwp</a>)</p>\n<p>6. Over 60 million people chose WordPress to power their website or blog. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>7. 14.7% of top 100 Websites are powered by WordPress. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/ultimate-list-of-wordpress-stats-facts-and-other-research/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>8. As of 2014, tens of thousands of new WordPress.com sites are created every day. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>9. There were 30 million Google searches for WordPress in December 2018. (<a href=\"https://trends.google.com/trends/explore?date=all&#038;q=blogger,drupal,sharepoint,wordpress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Google trends</a>)</p>\n<p>10. WordPress.com users produce about 136.2 million new blog posts and 77.7 million new comments each month. (WordPress)</p>\n<p>11. Over 409 million people view more than 20.7 billion blog pages on WordPress.com each month. (WordPress)</p>\n<p>12. Every day more than 1014 WordPress sites and 496 WooCommerce stores join the top 10 million websites tracked by W3Techs. (WPBeginner) </p>\n<p>13. WordPress is 10 times more popular than Joomla and 8.9 times more popular than Drupal. (Websitebuilder) </p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-development\">WordPress Development &#8211; Stats and Facts</h3>\n<p>WordPress has come a long way since it was introduced to the world. Check out these interesting WordPress statistics that showcase WordPress&#8217; development over the years and how it came to be what it is now. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_594103883.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-stats-development\" width=\"740\" height=\"493\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228178\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_594103883.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_594103883-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>1. WordPress was released by its founders Matt Mullenweg and Mike Little as a fork of b2/cafelog. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WordPress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wikipedia</a>) </p>\n<p>2. The first version of WordPress was released on May 27, 2003, which makes WordPress older than Twitter and Facebook. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>3. WordPress is not owned by any company. WordPress co-founder Matt Mullenweg created the non-profit organization, WordPress Foundation, to protect the freedoms offered by the software&#8217;s open source license. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>4. WordPress.org has no CEO. The project is run by volunteer developers from all over the world. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>5. Anyone can edit or add to WordPress’s core code as it is classified as open-source software licensed under the GPL. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/about/\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress.org</a>)</p>\n<p>6. WordPress is written in PHP programming language and uses MySQL for database. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>7. WordPress 5.0, the latest version of WordPress, has been downloaded 19,074,521 times so far. (Take a look at how fast the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/download/counter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress Counter</a> goes up!)</p>\n<p>8. A total of 98 versions of WordPress have been released to date. (<a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Current_events\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>9. 443 people contributed to WordPress 4.9, with 185 of them taking part for the first time. (<a href=\"https://www.codeinwp.com/blog/mesmerizing-wordpress-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">CodeinWP</a>)</p>\n<p>10. Only 22.4% of WordPress websites are running the most current version of the software (5.0). (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/about/stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.org</a>)</p>\n<p>11. Major core updates of WordPress are released about every 152 days on the average. (CodeinWP)</p>\n<p>12. The community behind WordPress also runs sister projects like bbPress, BuddyPress, and GlotPress. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>13. The WordPress software incorporates the programming languages PHP, MySQL, Javascript, HTML, and CSS. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-community\">WordPress Community &#8211; Stats and Facts</h3>\n<p>The WordPress community is full of diverse and passionate users. Take a look at these awesome statistics that demonstrate how plentiful and unique the WordPress community is. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_567871777.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-community-stats\" width=\"740\" height=\"413\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228190\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_567871777.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_567871777-300x167.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /> </p>\n<p>1. WordPress isn&#8217;t only for bloggers, businesses, and publications. Educational institutions like Cornell University, Harvard Blogs, The University of Maine, and Des Moines University are on WordPress. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/40-popular-universities-that-are-using-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>2. Some government websites that use WordPress include Sweden&#8217;s Official Site, Milwaukee Police News, United States Mission Geneva, and the Official Gazette of the Republic of the Philippines. (<a href=\"https://websitebuilder.org/resources/amazing-facts-you-probably-dont-know-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Websitebuilder</a>)</p>\n<p>3. Some <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/popular-big-name-brands-using-wordpress/\">notable users of WordPress.com</a> include TechCrunch, TED, CNN, The National Football League, UPS, and more. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>4. Other top websites and companies who use WordPress include Forbes, Mashable, The New York Times, Samsung, PlayStation, and Coca-Cola. (<a href=\"https://skilled.co/resources/28-facts-probably-dont-know-wordpress-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Skilled</a>)</p>\n<p>5. WordPress is most popular with businesses and least popular with news sites. (<a href=\"https://torquemag.io/2016/10/13-surprising-wordpress-statistics-updated-2016/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Torque</a>) </p>\n<p>6. Celebrities who use WordPress include Jay Z, Russel Brand, Sylvester Stallone, and Kobe Bryant. (<a href=\"https://skilled.co/resources/28-facts-probably-dont-know-wordpress-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Skilled</a>) </p>\n<p>7. WordPress is fully translated into 68 languages and partially translated into dozens more. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>8. English downloads are now officially surpassed by non-English downloads of WordPress software. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.org</a>)</p>\n<p>9. WordPress.com hosts blogs written in over 120 languages. The top languages are English at 71%, Spanish at 4.7%, Indonesian at 2.4%, and Portuguese (Brazil) at 2.3%. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>10. There are 2,030,000+ topics on the official WordPress support forum. (Codeinwp)</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-events\">WordPress Events &#8211; Facts and Statistics</h3>\n<p>WordPress fans all of the world get together to learn from each other at WordPress events like WordCamp. Check out these stats that show how the love of WordPress brings people together. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordcamp-events.png\" alt=\"wordpress-stats-events-wordcamp-\" width=\"740\" height=\"366\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228163\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordcamp-events.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordcamp-events-300x148.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>1. The first WordCamp was organized in San Francisco by Matt Mullenweg in 2006. (<a href=\"https://central.wordcamp.org/about/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordCamp</a>)</p>\n<p>2. There have been 932 WordCamps so far, in 65 countries. (<a href=\"https://central.wordcamp.org/about/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordCamp</a>)</p>\n<p>3. All WordCamp organizers and speakers are unpaid volunteers &#8212; they do it for the love of WordPress. (<a href=\"https://central.wordcamp.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordCamp</a>)</p>\n<p>4. The WordCamp event in Europe 2017 saw a record gathering of 1900 people coming from over 79 countries. (<a href=\"https://www.softwarefindr.com/wordpress-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SoftwareFindr</a>)</p>\n<p>5. If you can&#8217;t make it to a WordCamp event in person, you can watch recordings of the events for free on WordPress.tv. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.tv/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.tv</a>) </p>\n<p>6. Hundreds of thousands of WordPress users gather at monthly meetups in 436 cities worldwide. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>7. Besides WordCamp events, there are a ton of other WordPress events happening all the time, all over the world. Get a list of upcoming events on <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/community/events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.org</a>.  </p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-plugins\">WordPress Plugins &#8211; Stats, Facts, and Figures</h3>\n<p>WordPress plugins are like apps for your WordPress website. You can use plugins to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\">make a WordPress website</a> even more powerful than it already is. Check out these fascinating stats and facts about WordPress plugins. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-plugins.png\" alt=\"wordpress-plugin-stats\" width=\"740\" height=\"398\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228189\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-plugins.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-plugins-300x161.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /> </p>\n<p>1. WordPress plugin downloads crossed 1.48 Billion total downloads in 2016. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>2. There are 54,257 free plugins in the official WordPress Plugin Directory, with more added every day. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>3. Some of the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-plugins/\">most popular free WordPress plugins</a> are Contact Form 7, Yoast SEO, Akismet Anti-Spam, and Jetpack by WordPress.com, all with over 5 million active installations each. (WordPress.org)</p>\n<p>4. One of the most popular paid plugins for WordPress is Visual Composer with 2340 units sold per week. (<a href=\"https://skilled.co/resources/28-facts-probably-dont-know-wordpress-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Skilled</a>) </p>\n<p>5. There are over 6,000 premium WordPress plugins on CodeCanyon. Visual Composer, Slider Revolution, LayerSlider, and UberMenu are the best sellers. (Codeinwp)</p>\n<p>6. On CodeCanyon, 80% of searches are focused on functionality (i.e. sliders, forms, calendars). (Codeinwp)</p>\n<p>7. The most <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-ecommerce-plugins-compared/\">popular eCommerce plugin</a>, WooCommerce, is installed on more than 3 million websites with over 58 million all time downloads. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>8. Woocommerce powers 9% of all online stores. (<a href=\"https://trends.builtwith.com/shop/traffic/Entire-Internet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Built With</a>)</p>\n<p>9. The most popular free page builder is Elementor with over 430,000 new downloads every week. (<a href=\"https://www.softwarefindr.com/wordpress-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SoftwareFindr</a>)</p>\n<p>10. Hello Dolly is a completely useless but quite iconic plugin. The plugin displays a random lyric from the song Hello Dolly by Louis Armstrong in the upper right corner of your admin screen. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/what-is-the-hello-dolly-wordpress-plugin-should-you-delete-it/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-themes\">WordPress Themes &#8211; Statistics, Facts, and Figures</h3>\n<p>WordPress themes give your website an instant makeover. There are thousands of free and paid <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-business-themes/\">WordPress themes</a> you can download to give your website the exact look you want. Take a look at these stats about WordPress themes.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-themes-stats.png\" alt=\"wordpress-stats-themes\" width=\"740\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228167\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-themes-stats.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wordpress-themes-stats-300x170.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>1. Themes were first introduced in 2005, with the first new default WordPress theme called Kubrick. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/ultimate-list-of-wordpress-stats-facts-and-other-research/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WPBeginner</a>) </p>\n<p>2. WordPress releases a new default theme every year. (<a href=\"https://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/editorial/from-kubrick-to-twenty-sixteen-a-history-of-wordpress-default-themes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Elegant Themes</a>)</p>\n<p>3. WordPress.org’s free theme directory has more than 5,800 free WordPress themes. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/ultimate-list-of-wordpress-stats-facts-and-other-research/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WPBeginner</a>) </p>\n<p>4. The most popular WordPress theme is a tie between Divi and Genesis, each are used on 10% of all WordPress sites, for a total of 20%. (<a href=\"https://smallbiztrends.com/2017/02/most-popular-wordpress-themes.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Small Biz Trends</a>) </p>\n<p>5. Thousands of themes are sold by Commercial WordPress theme shops with an average price of $40 per theme. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>6. Avada by ThemeForest is one of the most purchased WordPress themes of all time with over 450,000 customers. (<a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">ThemeForest</a>)</p>\n<p>7. 25% of all WordPress themes on ThemeForest have made at least $2,500 in a month. And 50% of their themes have made at least $1,000 in a month. (<a href=\"https://envato.com/blog/envatos-insider-information-wordpress-economy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Envato</a>)</p>\n<p>8. 93% of overall ThemeForest sales come from responsive themes. (Codeinwp)</p>\n<p>9. Over 70% of ThemeForest searches are focused around niche themes. (Codeinwp)</p>\n<p>10. 2,125,962 is the number of times users switched their WordPress theme in the month of September 2018 alone. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/misc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.com</a>)</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-security\">WordPress Security &#8211; Statistics and Facts</h3>\n<p>Since WordPress is the most popular CMS software in the world, it&#8217;s a common target for hacking attempts. There are a number of ways to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" target=\"_blank\">protect your WordPress website</a> including keeping your plugins updated and choosing a strong password, but here are some statistics about WordPress security you should know.  </p>\n<p>1. 83% of all CMS based websites that were hacked in 2017 were running WordPress, which makes sense since WordPress holds 60% of the CMS market share. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>2. 39% of hacked WordPress websites were using an outdated version of the software. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>3. Almost 50% WordPress sites are affected by a security vulnerability caused by an outdated or poorly coded WordPress plugin or theme. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>4. 52% of reported WordPress security vulnerabilities relate to WordPress plugins. (<a href=\"https://www.keycdn.com/blog/wordpress-security\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">KeyCDN</a>)</p>\n<p>5. A WordPress plugin vulnerablity led to the Panama Papers Leak, the largest journalist data breach in history with over 4.8 million emails exploited. (<a href=\"https://www.wordfence.com/blog/2016/04/panama-papers-wordpress-email-connection/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wordfence</a>)</p>\n<p>6. Around 8% of WordPress sites were hacked due to a weak password. (WPBeginner)</p>\n<p>7. Only 11.45% of WordPress sites use SSL Encryption as of 2016. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>8. Google blacklists around 20,000 websites for malware, and around 50,000 for phishing, every single week. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>9. Wordfence blocked 3,236,017,356 attacks on WordPress sites in the last 30 days. (<a href=\"https://www.wordfence.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wordfence</a>)</p>\n<p>10. The four most common WordPress malware infections are Backdoors, Drive-by downloads, Pharma hacks, and Malicious redirects. (<a href=\"https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/10/four-malware-infections-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Smashing Magazine</a>)</p>\n<p>11. WordPress has a built-in Auto Update System that automatically updates itself for minor releases and can push automatic plugin updates if a severe vulnerability is found. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-economy\">WordPress Economy &#8211; Stats, Facts, and Figures</h3>\n<p>WordPress powers a multi-billion dollar economy and creates thousands of jobs all over the world. Check out these awesome statistics about the WordPress economy that prove you can make money from WordPress too.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_1259385493.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-economy-statistics\" width=\"740\" height=\"577\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228191\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_1259385493.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/shutterstock_1259385493-300x234.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" />  </p>\n<p>1. WordPress powers a multi-billion dollar economy. Many companies and professionals all over the world sell WordPress based products, services, and solutions. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<p>2. The most profitable WordPress companies are Automattic with a revenue of $1.3 billion, followed by Envato at $94 million and WPEngine at $73 million. (<a href=\"https://websitebuilder.org/resources/amazing-facts-you-probably-dont-know-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Websitebuilder</a>) </p>\n<p>3. There are a number of ways individuals can make money from WordPress: as a WordPress website designer, plugin/theme developer, SEO freelancer, website maintenance freelancer, WordPress content writer, and more.</p>\n<p>4. The average salary for “Wordpress jobs” is $66,467. (<a href=\"https://www.simplyhired.com/salaries-k-wordpress-jobs.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SimplyHired</a>)</p>\n<p>5. The average salary for WordPress developers in the U.S. is $79,000. (<a href=\"https://skilled.co/resources/28-facts-probably-dont-know-wordpress-infographic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Skilled</a>)</p>\n<p>6. A client looking for a custom WordPress site usually pays between $3,000 and $15,000 dollars to a remote freelancer. (<a href=\"https://managewp.com/blog/statistics-about-wordpress-usage\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ManageWP</a>)</p>\n<p>7. A custom-built WordPress websites can cost up to $100,000. (<a href=\"https://poststatus.com/wordpress-website-cost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">PostStatus</a>)</p>\n<p>8. The top growing skills in the world of programming are PSD to WordPress and WordPress Plugins. (<a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/hiring/development/the-top-growing-and-declining-programming-skills/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Upwork</a>)</p>\n<p>9. A Google search for &#8216;WordPress jobs&#8217; turns up about 1,250,000 results. (Google)</p>\n<p>10. 243,161 WordPress projects have been completed on Freelancer.com as of January 2015. That’s a total value of $60,571,205. (Codeinwp)</p>\n<p>11. 25% of WordPress users make a full-time living off of the CMS. (<a href=\"https://torquemag.io/2016/10/13-surprising-wordpress-statistics-updated-2016/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Torque</a>)</p>\n<h3 id=\"miscellaneous-wordpress\">Miscellaneous WordPress Stats and Facts</h3>\n<p>There are so many awesome stats and facts about WordPress that they can&#8217;t all possibly fit into a particular category. So, here are some miscellaneous WordPress stats for you to check out as well. </p>\n<p>1. WordPress.com receives over 20,000 support requests in an average month. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/misc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>2. 70,399,151 files were uploaded to WordPress.com in December 2018 alone. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/posting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.com</a>)</p>\n<p>3. Twitter was embedded on WordPress.com sites over 200,000 times last month. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/partners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.com</a>)</p>\n<p>4. Youtube was embedded on WordPress.com sites over 2 million times in December 2018 and Flickr was embedded over 3 million times the same month. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.com/activity/partners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.com</a>)</p>\n<p>5. The famous &#8216;W&#8217; WordPress logo was designed by Jason Santa Maria in 2005. (<a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/design/handbook/design-guide/foundations/identity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>)</p>\n<p>6. Christine Selleck Tremoulet, a prolific blogger and friend of WordPress co-founder Mullenweg, suggested the name WordPress. (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WordPress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wikipedia</a>)</p>\n<p>7. Wednesday is the most popular day for downloading WordPress, while Sunday is the least popular day. (<a href=\"https://wpcentral.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WPCentral</a>)</p>\n<p>8. WordPress can be installed in 5 minutes or less. (<a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress#Famous_5-Minute_Install\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress</a>) </p>\n<p>9. 83.5% of WordPress websites use Google Analytics. (<a href=\"https://websitebuilder.org/resources/amazing-facts-you-probably-dont-know-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Websitebuilder</a>)</p>\n<p>10. WordPress has built-in multisite feature which is hidden by default. It allows you to create a network of websites using the same WordPress installation. (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner</a>)</p>\n<h3 id=\"wordpress-fun\">Fun WordPress Stats and Facts</h3>\n<p>Finally, the world of WordPress is a fun place to be, so we understand if you can&#8217;t get enough of it. So, enjoy these random fun facts about WordPress. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wapuu-mascott-international.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-unofficial-mascot\" width=\"740\" height=\"287\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228162\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wapuu-mascott-international.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/wapuu-mascott-international-300x116.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>1. Wapuu is the unofficial mascot of WordPress, originally created by active members of the Japanese WordPress community. (<a href=\"https://torquemag.io/2017/08/wapuu-created-cultural-center-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Torque</a>)</p>\n<p>2. There’s a Wapuu for every WordCamp event and several other special variations of Wapuu as well. (<a href=\"https://wapu.us/wapuus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wapu.us</a>)</p>\n<p>3. The WordPress core developers are lovers of jazz music, so every major WordPress release is named after a famous jazz musician. (<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/about/roadmap/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WordPress.org</a>)</p>\n<p>4. The WordPress Wiggle is the unofficial dance of the WordPress people. The song was commissioned by Zack Katz of GravityView. (<a href=\"https://wpshout.com/links/do-the-wordpress-wiggle/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WPShout</a>)</p>\n<p>5. The company behind WordPress.com, Automattic, closed its beautiful San Francisco office because their employees stopped showing up. (<a href=\"https://qz.com/1002655/the-company-behind-wordpress-is-closing-its-gorgeous-san-francisco-office-because-its-employees-never-show-up/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quartz</a>)</p>\n<p>6. WordPress has been used to control a missile guidance system. (<a href=\"https://dd32.id.au/2010/06/12/wordpress-what-cant-it-do/strike-back-s01-e05-wordpress-1/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dion Hulse, Lead Developer @ WordPress)</a></p>\n<p>We hoped you enjoyed learning more about WordPress with these interesting WordPress statistics, facts, and research. If you still want to discover more amazing information, tips, and tricks about WordPress, you might want to read our article on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-start-a-blog-step-by-step/\">How to Start a Blog and Make Extra Income on the Side</a> (with WordPress). </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/interesting-wordpress-stats-facts/\">100+ Interesting WordPress Stats &#038; Facts (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://www.isitwp.com/interesting-wordpress-stats-facts/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:28:\"https://www.isitwp.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:18:{s:6:\"server\";s:17:\"Sucuri/Cloudproxy\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Sun, 03 Feb 2019 21:25:22 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:11:\"x-sucuri-id\";s:5:\"12003\";s:16:\"x-xss-protection\";s:13:\"1; mode=block\";s:15:\"x-frame-options\";s:10:\"SAMEORIGIN\";s:22:\"x-content-type-options\";s:7:\"nosniff\";s:25:\"strict-transport-security\";a:2:{i:0;s:44:\"max-age=31536000; includeSubdomains; preload\";i:1;s:13:\"max-age=86400\";}s:23:\"content-security-policy\";s:26:\"upgrade-insecure-requests;\";s:10:\"set-cookie\";s:98:\"srv_id=c22b625f94ce9b456550ebf299e3ae