ou to set up Google Optimize on your WordPress site hassle-free. In this tutorial, we’ll show you how to how to set up Google Optimize easily on your WordPress site. What Is Google Optimize? Google Optimize is a free A/B testing [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-set-up-google-optimize-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">How to Set Up Google Optimize in WordPress (the Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Shahzad Saeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10794:\"<p>Want to set up Google Optimize in WordPress? Just like Google Analytics, MonsterInsights allows you to set up Google Optimize on your WordPress site hassle-free. In this tutorial, we’ll show you how to how to set up Google Optimize easily on your WordPress site.</p>\n<h3>What Is Google Optimize?</h3>\n<p>Google Optimize is a free <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/easy-ab-testing-ideas/\">A/B testing</a> and personalization product by Google that lets you conveniently conduct experiments to see what works best on your site.</p>\n<p>Google Optimize is just right for small and medium-sized businesses that need powerful testing, but don&#8217;t have the budget or team resources for an enterprise-level solution.</p>\n<p>Best of all, it&#8217;s built right on top of <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-complete-beginners-guide-to-google-analytics-for-wordpress/\">Google Analytics</a>. With the Google Optimize setup, you can start using your Analytics data to conduct A/B tests and improve the user experience and conversions on your site right away.</p>\n<h3>How to Set Up Google Optimize in WordPress &#8211; Step-by-Step</h3>\n<p>In order to install Google Optimize on your site, you’ll need to insert a small code snippet into your website header. If you’re a beginner, it can be a bit tricky.</p>\n<p>Thankfully, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> has made the process very simple and beginner-friendly. It comes with a powerful <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/google-optimize/\">Google Optimize addon</a> that allows you to easily implement Google Optimize on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>If you don’t know what MonsterInsights is, it’s the most user-friendly Google Analytics plugin for WordPress.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157422\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"MonsterInsights best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It helps you to effortlessly set up Google Analytics in WordPress with just a few clicks. The plugin enables anyone to set up and use Google Analytics without touching any code.</p>\n<p>Having said that, let’s go ahead and see the steps to set up Google Optimize in WordPress (the easy way).</p>\n<h4>Step 1: Install MonsterInsights Google Optimize Addon</h4>\n<p>Before we get started with Optimize setup, make sure you&#8217;ve <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">properly installed Google Analytics on your site</a> with MonsterInsights.</p>\n<p>If you’ve already done that, you can go ahead and install the Google Optimize addon now.</p>\n<p>To install the addon, you’ll need to go to <strong>Insights » Addons</strong> first. Then, navigate to the MonsterInsights Google Optimize addon and click the <strong>Install</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-105144\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/install-google-optimize.jpg\" alt=\"install google optimize\" width=\"376\" height=\"474\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/install-google-optimize.jpg 376w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/install-google-optimize-238x300.jpg 238w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 376px) 100vw, 376px\" /></p>\n<p>Once it’s installed, click the <strong>Activate</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-105141\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/activate-google-optimize.jpg\" alt=\"activate google optimize\" width=\"377\" height=\"474\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/activate-google-optimize.jpg 377w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/activate-google-optimize-239x300.jpg 239w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 377px) 100vw, 377px\" /></p>\n<p>Now that the addon is installed and activated, you can access your Google Optimize settings and add the snippet code. We&#8217;ll show you how later on in this tutorial.</p>\n<h4>Step 2: Create a New Google Optimize Account</h4>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to create a new Google Optimize account. Go to <a href=\"https://optimize.google.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">optimize.google.com</a> and click <strong>Get Started</strong>.</p>\n<p>Now you’ll have to enter an <strong>Account Name</strong> and a <strong>Container Name</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103135\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/create-google-optimize-account.png\" alt=\"create google optimize account\" width=\"383\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/create-google-optimize-account.png 383w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/create-google-optimize-account-300x162.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px\" /></p>\n<p>An account allows you to run experiments on one or more domains you own. You’ll likely need only one account. The container is where all your experiments and configuration settings will live.</p>\n<p>For naming, here are our suggestions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Account Name:</strong> You may use your own name or your company name. (e.g. MonsterInsights)</li>\n<li><strong>Container Name:</strong> You may use the domain name of your site. (e.g. MonsterInsights.com)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Then, Agree to the Optimize Terms of Service and click <strong>Create</strong>.</p>\n<h4>Step 3: Link Your Optimize Account to Google Analytics</h4>\n<p>To link your Optimize account to your Google Analytics account, go to the <a href=\"https://optimize.google.com/optimize/home/#/accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Accounts page in Google Optimize</a> and click on a container.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103130\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/google-optimize-accounts-page.jpg\" alt=\"google optimize accounts page\" width=\"620\" height=\"248\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/google-optimize-accounts-page.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/google-optimize-accounts-page-300x120.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>In the Container information panel on the right-hand side, click on <strong>Link Property</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103133\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/click-link-property.jpg\" alt=\"click link property\" width=\"304\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/click-link-property.jpg 304w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/click-link-property-300x249.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 304px) 100vw, 304px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, select the Google Analytics property that corresponds to the site on which you’ll be running experiments.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103131\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/select-a-google-analytics-property-in-optimize.jpg\" alt=\"select a google analytics property in optimize\" width=\"620\" height=\"175\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/select-a-google-analytics-property-in-optimize.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/select-a-google-analytics-property-in-optimize-300x85.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h4>Step 4: Add Optimizer to Your Website</h4>\n<p>Now return to the <a href=\"https://optimize.google.com/optimize/home/#/accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Optimize accounts page</a> and copy your Optimize Container ID. This should be in the format GTM-XXXXXXX.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103134\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/copy-google-optimize-container-id.jpg\" alt=\"copy google optimize container id\" width=\"620\" height=\"248\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/copy-google-optimize-container-id.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/copy-google-optimize-container-id-300x120.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, log into your WordPress dashboard, and navigate to <strong>Insights » Settings » Conversions</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-176781\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/google-optimize-setup.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"981\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/google-optimize-setup.jpg 1080w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/google-optimize-setup-300x273.jpg 300w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/google-optimize-setup-768x698.jpg 768w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/google-optimize-setup-1024x930.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also click the checkbox near <strong>Enable Google Optimize Async Page Hide Compatibility</strong>.</p>\n<p>Doing so reduces the risk of page flickering (the original page appears briefly before loading the variation). It also ensures that users on slow connections have a better experience by only showing experiment variants when the Optimize container loads within the set timeout.</p>\n<p>You can leave the remaining field unchanged.</p>\n<p>Then, click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</p>\n<p>That’s it! You’ve successfully installed Google Optimize in WordPress.</p>\n<p>Before conducting experiments on your site, you might want to check out this beginner&#8217;s guide to <a href=\"http://optinmonster.com/conversion-optimization-101-split-testing-vs-multivariate-testing/\">conversion optimization 101: split testing vs. multivariate testing</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-set-up-google-optimize-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">How to Set Up Google Optimize in WordPress (the Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-set-up-google-optimize-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:116:\"Introducing MonsterInsights 7.4 – New Setup Wizard, Improved Affiliate Tracking, MemberPress Integration, and More\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:139:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-monsterinsights-7-4/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=introducing-monsterinsights-7-4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-monsterinsights-7-4/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 15 Jan 2019 17:06:15 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=179051\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:720:\"<p>Today, I&#8217;m proud to announce MonsterInsights 7.4, our first release of 2019. It comes with a lot of exciting features that you&#8217;ve been asking for including a brand new setup wizard, MemberPress integration, improved affiliate link tracking, and more. Let&#8217;s take a look at what&#8217;s new in MonsterInsights 7.4&#8230; MonsterInsights Setup Wizard It is our [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-monsterinsights-7-4/\">Introducing MonsterInsights 7.4 &#8211; New Setup Wizard, Improved Affiliate Tracking, MemberPress Integration, and More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Syed Balkhi\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7569:\"<p>Today, I&#8217;m proud to announce MonsterInsights 7.4, our first release of 2019. It comes with a lot of exciting features that you&#8217;ve been asking for including a brand new setup wizard, MemberPress integration, improved affiliate link tracking, and more.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at what&#8217;s new in MonsterInsights 7.4&#8230;</p>\n<h3>MonsterInsights Setup Wizard</h3>\n<p>It is our mission to make Google Analytics easy for WordPress sites, so you can get the stats matter and grow your business.</p>\n<p>Our brand new setup wizard, makes MonsterInsights even easier than it already was.</p>\n<p>Now when you first install MonsterInsights, you have the option to use our five-step setup wizard to properly add Google Analytics on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179060\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsights-setupwizard.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights New Setup Wizard\" width=\"620\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsights-setupwizard.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsights-setupwizard-300x254.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>It starts by asking you the category of your website. Based on your selection, our setup wizard recommends optimal settings for MonsterInsights.</p>\n<p>With our new setup wizard, you can setup Google Analytics on your website like a Pro (in less than 5 minutes).</p>\n<h3>Brand New Settings Panel</h3>\n<p>With MonsterInsights 7.4, you will notice a brand new settings panel that&#8217;s not only simpler, but extremely FAST.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179065\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsights-settingspanel-1.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights New Settings Panel\" width=\"620\" height=\"485\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsights-settingspanel-1.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsights-settingspanel-1-300x235.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>We redesigned the settings panel based on user-feedback to better organize and simplify the options that are available.</p>\n<p>Over the years, we added a lot of tracking options and features which made our old settings panel difficult to use.</p>\n<p>The problem was that our settings were divided based on features and addons instead of actual use-cases.</p>\n<p>The new settings panel is organized based on solutions which offers a much better user experience.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179062\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/mi-newsettingspanel-comparison.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights New Settings Panel Comparison\" width=\"620\" height=\"380\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/mi-newsettingspanel-comparison.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/mi-newsettingspanel-comparison-300x184.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Aside from ease of use, you will notice that the new Settings panel is extremely fast. That&#8217;s because our dev team used Vue.js programming language which offers significant performance improvements.</p>\n<h3>Improved Affiliate Tracking</h3>\n<p>If you <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/start-a-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">make money from your blog</a> using affiliate links, then you&#8217;re going to love our improved affiliate tracking feature.</p>\n<p>One of the big reasons why bloggers love MonsterInsights is because we make it easy to track all outbound links in WordPress. This helps you uncover new partnership opportunities.</p>\n<p>Our old affiliate tracking feature also made it easy to track your custom branded affiliate links, but the problem was that you were limited to only one prefix (i.e /go/ or /refer/).</p>\n<p>With our new improved affiliate tracking, you can now define multiple internal paths to be tracked as affiliate links. This is extremely helpful if you&#8217;re using an affiliate link management plugin like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/pretty-links-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Pretty Links</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179067\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/affiliate-link-tracking.png\" alt=\"Affiliate Link Tracking\" width=\"620\" height=\"292\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/affiliate-link-tracking.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/affiliate-link-tracking-300x141.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>MemberPress Integration</h3>\n<p>If you run a <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/ultimate-guide-to-creating-a-wordpress-membership-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">membership site</a> using MemberPress, then you are going to love this integration.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">MemberPress</a> is one of the most popular membership plugin for WordPress. That&#8217;s why in MonsterInsights 7.4, we have built an Enhanced Ecommerce Integration for MemberPress, so you can grow your membership site with confidence.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179084\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsightsmemberpress.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Integration for MemberPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"145\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsightsmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/monsterinsightsmemberpress-300x70.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Google Analytics Enhanced Ecommerce tracking allows you to see important eCommerce metrics like total revenue, conversion rate, average order value, top products, top referral sources, and more.</p>\n<p>Now you can get all your important store metrics right inside your WordPress dashboard in a single report.</p>\n<p>All you need to do is <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/enable-ecommerce-tracking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">enable eCommerce tracking</a> inside your Google Analytics account, and then install the MonsterInsights Ecommerce Addon.</p>\n<p>Once activated, MonsterInsights will automatically add the right tracking tags to your website, so you can have your eCommerce tracking data within minutes.</p>\n<p>No need to spend hours configuring Google Analytis Ecommerce tracking. MonsterInsights does it for you, with just a few clicks.</p>\n<p>We hope you enjoy these features. We have a lot more in the works that I can’t wait to share with you in the upcoming weeks.</p>\n<p>As always, thank you for continued support of MonsterInsights. We look forward to continue making analytics easy for you!</p>\n<p><em>Syed and the MonsterInsights team</em></p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t have a MonsterInsights Pro license? <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">Click here to get started today</a>, and experience the power, and ease, of MonsterInsights.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-monsterinsights-7-4/\">Introducing MonsterInsights 7.4 &#8211; New Setup Wizard, Improved Affiliate Tracking, MemberPress Integration, and More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-monsterinsights-7-4/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"How to Find Your Average eCommerce Order Value in Google Analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:209:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 14 Jan 2019 16:00:17 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"ecommerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"aov\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"metrics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=101026\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:645:\"<p>Do you want to know the average value of each eCommerce transaction in your online store? You can easily find out by looking at the Average Order Value metrics in Google Analytics. In this article, we’ll show you how to find your average eCommerce order value in Google Analytics. What is Average Order Value? Average [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/\">How to Find Your Average eCommerce Order Value in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Shahzad Saeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11741:\"<p>Do you want to know the average value of each eCommerce transaction in your online store? You can easily find out by looking at the <strong>Average Order Value</strong> metrics in Google Analytics. In this article, we’ll show you how to find your average eCommerce order value in Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>What is Average Order Value?</h3>\n<p><strong>Average Order Value (AOV)</strong> is a metric that tells you the average value of an eCommerce transaction in your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-woocommerce-store/\">online store</a>. In other words, it tells you, on average, how much revenue each order brings in.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s calculated as follows:</p>\n<p>Average Order Value = Product Revenue / Total Transactions</p>\n<h3>Why is Calculating Average Order Value Important?</h3>\n<p>Just like conversion rate, average order value is also an important key performance indicator (KPI) that&#8217;s vital to your online business.</p>\n<p>For instance, by improving your conversion rate, you’re encouraging more users to buy from your store. Similarly, by improving average order value, you’re enticing your customers to spend more whenever they make a purchase.</p>\n<p>That means, aside from conversion rate, you’ll also have to focus on average order value in order to <strong>increase sales and revenue from your eCommerce store</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to Find Average Order Value of Your Store</h3>\n<p>You can find the average order value of your WordPress store in the following places:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Inside Your WordPress Dashboard (With MonsterInsights)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>In Your Google Analytics Account</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Of the 2 methods, it&#8217;s far more convenient to view your report inside your WordPress dashboard. You don&#8217;t need to navigate away from your site or log into another website to view your reports.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re wondering how that&#8217;s possible, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> is the answer. It&#8217;s the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-151922\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/monsterinsights-wp-google-analytics-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Best Google Analytics Plugin for WordPress\" width=\"560\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/monsterinsights-wp-google-analytics-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/monsterinsights-wp-google-analytics-plugin-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights makes it very easy to install and use Google Analytics on your WordPress site. Even an absolute beginner can easily set up Google Analytics and track their important website metrics using this plugin.</p>\n<p>Best of all, it allows you to see all of your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\">website reports right inside your WordPress dashboard</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want to know more about how MonsterInsights makes Google Analytics simple, read our detailed post on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analytics-whats-the-real-difference/\">MonsterInsights vs. Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p>Having said that, let’s get started with setting up eCommerce tracking in Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>Enable eCommerce Tracking in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>First of all, you’ll need to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">set up Google Analytics on your site</a>.</p>\n<p>Next, you’ll need to enable eCommerce tracking in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-login-to-google-analytics/\">Sign into your Google Analytics account</a> and click the <strong>Admin</strong> menu in the right menu bar.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-98965\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/admin.jpg\" alt=\"Click admin menu in Google Analytics\" width=\"255\" height=\"281\" /></p>\n<p>Then, navigate to <strong>eCommerce Settings</strong> under the View column.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89944\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ecommerce-settings.jpg\" alt=\"click ecommerce settings under the right hand column\" width=\"540\" height=\"316\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ecommerce-settings.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ecommerce-settings-300x176.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, the eCommerce setup window will open.</p>\n<p>Turn on <strong>Enable eCommerce</strong> first. Then, turn on <strong>Enhanced eCommerce Settings</strong> and click the Submit button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89946\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings.png\" alt=\"submit your ecommerce tracking settings\" width=\"306\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings.png 306w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings-296x300.png 296w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/submit-ecommerce-settings-100x100.png 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 306px) 100vw, 306px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, open your WordPress dashboard and navigate to <strong>Insights » Addons</strong>. Then, install and activate <strong>MonsterInsights eCommerce</strong> in just 2 clicks.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89800\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-ecommerce-addon.jpg\" alt=\"install ecommerce addon\" width=\"540\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-ecommerce-addon.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-ecommerce-addon-300x132.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, MonsterInsights will automatically detect your eCommerce plugin (WooCommerce or Easy Digital Downloads) and start tracking all your eCommerce data including the order value.</p>\n<p>You can check on that by going to <strong>Insights » Settings » Tracking</strong> and clicking on the <strong>eCommerce</strong> tab.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175294\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"581\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/monsterinsights-ecommerce-settings-300x281.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Make sure that there’s a check mark on <strong>Use Enhanced eCommerce</strong> and your plugin is detected. Then click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n<p>Now, Google Analytics will start gathering data on your eCommerce sales.</p>\n<h3>View Your Average eCommerce Order Value in Your Dashboard</h3>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve completed setting up your eCommerce tracking, you can check your reports after a few hours have passed. Google Analytics usually takes 24-48 hours to gather the complete data you&#8217;ll need.</p>\n<p>With <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">MonsterInsights</a>, it&#8217;s really easy to view your eCommerce reports because it allows you to see the most important data directly inside your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>To view your eCommerce reports, go to <strong>Insights » Reports</strong> from your dashboard and click the <strong>eCommerce</strong> tab at the top.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179103\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/avgordervaluemiecommercereport.jpg\" alt=\"Average Order Value in MonsterInsights eCommerce Reports\" width=\"560\" height=\"386\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/avgordervaluemiecommercereport.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/avgordervaluemiecommercereport-300x207.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see in the screenshot above, you’ll see your eCommerce store’s average order value along with your conversion rate, total transactions, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-most-popular-ecommerce-products-in-google-analytics/\">top products</a>, etc.</p>\n<p>Next, we’ll show you how to see that same report in Google Analytics.</p>\n<h3>Find Your Average Order Value in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>First, visit the official Google Analytics website and log into your Analytics account.</p>\n<p>To view the AOV of your entire site, navigate to <strong>Conversions » eCommerce » Overview.</strong> You&#8217;ll see the metric <strong>Avg. Order Value </strong>along with many other metrics.</p>\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-101028\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/average-order-value-of-entire-site.jpg\" alt=\"average-order-value-of-entire-site\" width=\"560\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/average-order-value-of-entire-site.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/average-order-value-of-entire-site-300x154.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></h3>\n<h3>Finding Average eCommerce Order Value by Traffic Source</h3>\n<p>To view AOV by traffic sources, navigate to <strong>Acquisition » All Traffic » Source/Medium</strong>.</p>\n<p>Then click on <strong>E-commerce</strong> under the Explorer tab. In the table, you can see the <strong>Avg. Order Value</strong> column.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-101027\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ecommerce-order-value-from-traffic-sources.jpg\" alt=\"average ecommerce order value by traffic source\" width=\"560\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ecommerce-order-value-from-traffic-sources.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ecommerce-order-value-from-traffic-sources-300x176.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>When you know which traffic sources are bringing in the highest average order values, you can focus your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/woocommerce-marketing-tools-to-grow-your-business/\">marketing</a> efforts on what works and figure out how to optimize your other traffic sources.</p>\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you to find the average eCommerce order value of your store.</p>\n<p>If you’re looking to boost sales and revenue from your store, you’ll enjoy reading this guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/ecommerce-customer-retention-strategies/\">eCommerce customer retention strategies</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/\">How to Find Your Average eCommerce Order Value in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-average-ecommerce-order-value-in-google-analytics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";